OL,3,CPolice admit they might take your car
OL,4,Ckeys to protect you from theft
OL,6,FIf your car keys have been taken, you
OL,7,Fmay think you are the victim of a
OL,8,Fcrime but in Jersey, the police force
OL,9,Fis hoping to beat joyriders by swiping
OL,10,Fthem first.
OL,12,FThe island has a low crime rate
OL,13,Fcompared to the UK, so some residents
OL,14,Fleave their vehicles unlocked with the
OL,15,Fkeys inside or nearby.
OL,17,FHowever, officers say there has been a
OL,18,Frise in groups of unlicensed young
OL,19,Fpeople taking cars and putting other
OL,20,Froad users, as well as themselves, at
OL,21,Frisk.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/6
